{
  "local_port": 34878,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some Facebook tips and hacks?",
  "response": "Here are some useful Facebook tips and hacks to enhance your experience on the platform:\n\n---\n\n### **Privacy and Security Tips**\n1. **Customize Your Privacy Settings**:  \n   - Go to **Settings & Privacy** > **Privacy Shortcuts** to control who sees your posts, friends list, and profile information.\n   - Use the **\"Limit Past Posts\"** feature to change older posts to \"Friends Only.\"\n\n2. **Review Tagged Posts**:  \n   - Enable the **\"Timeline and Tagging\"** settings to review posts you're tagged in before they appear on your profile.\n\n3. **Block Unwanted Users**:  \n   - Use the **Blocking** section in settings to block specific people, apps, or pages.\n\n4. **Secure Your Account**:  \n   - Enable **Two-Factor Authentication** (2FA) for added security.\n\n5. **Control Who Can Message You**:  \n   - Adjust message delivery settings to filter messages from non-friends into your **Message Requests** folder.\n\n---\n\n### **Navigation and Organization Tips**\n6. **Use Facebook Shortcuts**:  \n   - Press \"J\" and \"K\" to scroll through news feed posts or \"L\" to like a post.\n   \n7. **Create Friend Lists**:  \n   - Organize your friends into custom lists (e.g., Close Friends, Work) to control who sees specific posts.\n\n8. **Save Posts for Later**:  \n   - Click the three dots on a post and select **Save** to bookmark it for future viewing.\n\n9. **Find Old Posts Quickly**:  \n   - Use the **Activity Log** to search for posts, photos, or comments you\u2019ve made in the past.\n\n10. **Turn Off Auto-Playing Videos**:  \n   - Go to **Settings** > **Videos** > **Auto-Play** to disable or limit video autoplay.\n\n---\n\n### **Posting and Engagement Hacks**\n11. **Schedule Posts**:  \n   - If you manage a Page, use Facebook\u2019s **Publishing Tools** to schedule posts in advance.\n\n12. **Edit Posts After Publishing**:  \n   - Click the three dots on your post and select **Edit** to make changes.\n\n13. **Use Reactions Strategically**:  \n   - Long-press the Like button to access other reactions (Love, Wow, Laugh, Sad, Angry).\n\n14. **Post High-Quality Content**:  \n   - Use Facebook\u2019s **Creative Hub** to test and preview ads or posts before publishing.\n\n---\n\n### **Messaging Tips**\n15. **Send Temporary Messages**:  \n   - Tap the clock icon while sending a message to enable **Disappearing Messages** (24-hour timer).\n\n16. **Use Messenger Effects**:  \n   - Add effects like confetti, balloons, or sound effects to messages by typing specific words (e.g., \"congrats\" or \"woohoo\").\n\n17. **Share Live Location**:  \n   - In Messenger, click the location icon to share your live location with friends for a set time.\n\n---\n\n### **Hidden Features and Tricks**\n18. **See Your \"On This Day\" Memories**:  \n   - Visit **Facebook Memories** to see posts, photos, and events from past years.\n\n19. **Find Hidden Games**:  \n   - Search for \"Facebook Gaming\" to discover and play games directly on the platform.\n\n20. **Use Facebook Stories Highlights**:  \n   - Save your Stories to **Highlights** on your profile to keep them visible beyond 24 hours.\n\n21. **Find Wi-Fi Nearby**:  \n   - Go to **More** > **Find Wi-Fi** to locate free or public Wi-Fi spots near you.\n\n---\n\n### **Ad and Algorithm Hacks**\n22. **Customize Your Ad Preferences**:  \n   - Go to **Settings** > **Ads** > **Ad Preferences** to manage your interests and control the ads you see.\n\n23. **Prioritize Friends and Pages**:  \n   - Use the **News Feed Preferences** to prioritize posts from specific friends or Pages.\n\n24. **Hide Ads**:  \n   - Click the three dots on an ad and select **Hide Ad** to reduce similar ads.\n\n---\n\n### **Fun and Creative Hacks**\n25. **Change Your Name Temporarily**:  \n   - Go to **Settings** > **Personal Information** to change your name for a special occasion or event.\n\n26. **Add a Nickname**:  \n   - Edit your profile to add a nickname that appears in parentheses next to your name.\n\n27. **Use Invisible Mode in Messenger**:  \n   - Turn off your active profile by enabling **Invisible Mode** in Messenger settings.\n\n28. **Create Custom Emojis with Bitmoji**:  \n   - Link your Bitmoji account to Messenger to use personalized stickers in chats.\n\n---\n\nBy using these tips and hacks, you can make your Facebook experience more efficient, secure, and enjoyable!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
